column5: Dang Terry!!! I thought you had gone fishin' and were going to show us some fish porn!
WOw, that's really fast..Three days ago it was still full of ice.. The rain must have washed everything through!
Are panfish open year round in Simcoe?
I think that`s all the perch moving in        how the heck would I know what it is
However, all that brown area you see surrounding the lake shows where you aren't allowed to park.
Just stay off the west side.
And the perchin' begins! Hoping to have the boat ready by the 13th
I picked mine up yesterday now I just need to put everything together
I'll be out on wed for some perchin.......I haven't fished in almost 2 weeks, I'm going stir crazy now.  Sinker
it must be submerged ice.... maybe????? cause any other time i've seen simcoe with open water on that site, it's all dark blue.
